openpas.basics

Interface SymbolicResolver

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    NumericResolver
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ImplicateResolver

    public interface SymbolicResolver
    This defines operations that relate to finding symbolic solutions to hypotheses in PAS. These symbolic solutions are needed in numerical calculations.

      • findQS

        Expressions.SimpleSentence<LogicalOps.LogicalOr,LogicalOps.LogicalAnd> findQS(Expressions.SimpleSentence<LogicalOps.LogicalAnd,LogicalOps.LogicalOr> hypothesis)
        Finds the quasi-support (QS) for a given CNF hypothesis. The QS alone is normally needed to calculate the various degrees of support (see NumericResolver#calcDQS(SimpleSentence) for more).
        Parameters:
        hypothesis -
        Returns:

      • findSP

        Expressions.SimpleSentence<LogicalOps.LogicalOr,LogicalOps.LogicalAnd> findSP(Expressions.SimpleSentence<LogicalOps.LogicalAnd,LogicalOps.LogicalOr> hypothesis)
        Finds the support for a given CNF hypothesis. This is normally interesting only for symbolic analysis and not required for numerical calculations (see NumericResolver#calcNormalisedDSP(SimpleSentence) for more).
